\begin_inset Formula $2$
\end_inset

 must be indifferent between 
\begin_inset Formula $l$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 so it must be that
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
p(L)+2p(R) & =2p(R)\\
p(L)+p(R) & =1\end{align*}

\end_inset

 so 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
p(L) & =0\\
p(R) & =1\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 must at least prefer R to L so 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
