\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 is better off playing 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 so the belief that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(R)=0$
\end_inset

 is not sustainable.
 We can thus eliminate the possibility that a belief such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(R)=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(L)=\mu(M)$
\end_inset

 could be sustained under a SPNE.
 
\end_layout

